# Mapping Study Toolbox Context

## High-level architecture
- Runtime stack: Node.js + Express + Sequelize + sqlite3 + TypeScript.
- API entrypoint: `server.ts` (API-only service mounted under `/api`).
- API router: `routes/api.ts` with handlers in:
  - `routes/records.ts`
  - `routes/mappingQuestions.ts`
- UI source code lives in `ui/` (Vue 3 + Vite + Pinia + Handsontable).
- Shared API contract types live in `shared/contracts.ts`.
- Default dev runtime is docker-compose (`docker-compose.yml`) with backend + frontend watch mode.

## Runtime topology
- Backend API: `http://localhost:3000/api`
- Frontend dev server: `http://localhost:8080`
- Backend does not serve UI assets in development.
- UI production build output: `ui/dist`.

## Data model snapshot
- `Record`: bibliographic and classification fields (`title`, `author`, `url`, `abstract`, `status`, `comment`, `databases`, `alternateUrls`, `editedBy`) plus enrichment fields (DOI, references, citations, topics, affiliations).
- `Forum`: venue metadata (`name`, `publisher`, `issn`, `jufoLevel`, aliases).
- `MappingQuestion`: mapping metadata (`title`, `type`, `position`).
- `MappingOption`: option value (`title`, `position`, `color`, `mappingQuestionId`).
- `RecordMappingOption`: join table (`recordId`, `mappingQuestionId`, `mappingOptionId`).
- `Import`: import metadata table retained for compatibility.

## Contract-critical behavior
- `GET /api/records` -> `{ count, records }`.
- `GET /api/records` is list-optimized by default: heavy enrichment arrays are omitted unless `withDetails=1`.
- `GET /api/mapping-questions` -> `{ count, questions }`.
- Record payload include aliases expected by UI: `Forum`, `MappingOptions`.
- Record status domain: `null | uncertain | excluded | included`.
- Mapping question/option ordering is position-driven.
- Data tab partial updates use `PATCH /api/records/:id`.
- Enrichment jobs:
  - `POST /api/records/enrichment-jobs`
  - `GET /api/records/enrichment-jobs/:jobId` (supports compact polling via `compact=1&resultCursor=&updatedCursor=`)
  - `POST /api/records/enrichment-jobs/:jobId/cancel`

## Operational notes
- Configuration template: `config/config.example.json`.
- Local runtime config: `config/config.json`.
- Migrations are authoritative history; never rewrite old migration files.
- Add new migration files for schema changes.

## Quality and automation
- Backend checks:
  - `npm run typecheck`
  - `npm test`
- Frontend checks:
  - `npm run ui:typecheck`
  - `npm run ui:test`
  - `npm run ui:lint`
  - `npm run ui:build`
